            <bug_when>2014-05-08 18:22:31 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>In IE10, pointer events have several properties like MSPOINTER_TYPE_MOUSE that are needed to determine the pointer type. qx.event.type.Pointer._cloneNativeEvent didn&#39;t copy these properties so getPointerType() always returned an empty String. This broke the quickSelection mode of the SelectBox&#39; list, which checks if the pointerType is &#39;mouse&#39;.

Fixed with 0b584c1874e3e593c721dea96e300c06f310f827</thetext>
